The paper deals with the design of passive beamforming in wireless communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The proposed approach uses deep learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of reconfigurable intelligent surfaces (RIS), which is a technology related to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The approach is designed to make real-time predictions, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents simulation results, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
